---
title: Empty States
---

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h1>Empty States</h1>
    <p>We often have empty lists or content where we need to alert the user to perform a certain action to populate the list. There are two types: simple, and complex</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Empty State Default</h2>
    <div class="example">
      <section class="Box EmptyState">
        <img  class="EmptyState-image" src="/images/buoy/empty-team.svg">
        <h3>Invite team members to your account.</h3>
        <p>Inviting team members allows you to create shared resources<br>and work collaboratively, without having to share a login.</p>
        <a class="Button Button--blue">Invite Team Members</a>
      </section>
    </div>
    <pre>
      <code><%= display_code('
<section class="Box EmptyState">
  <img  class="EmptyState-image" src="/images/buoy/empty-team.svg">
  <h3>Invite team members to your account.</h3>
  <p>Inviting team members allows you to create shared resources and work collaboratively, without having to share a login.</p>
  <a class="Button Button--blue">Invite Team Members</a>
</section>') %></code>
    </pre>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="row u-mb-5">
  <div class="small-12 columns">
    <h2>Empty State Simple</h2>
    <p>The simple empty states is good for instances when a full empty state is too much, and an alert isn't needed.</p>
    <div class="example">
      <section class="EmptyState--simple">
        <p class="u-mb-0">Thanks! Please add a credit card to activate your account.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
    <pre>
      <code><%= display_code('
<section class="EmptyState--simple">
  <p class="u-mb-0">Empty state text here...</p>
</section>') %></code>
    </pre>
  </div>
</div>
